<doc id="1158166" wikidata="Q6658856" url="?curid=1158166" title="Livia Drusa">
<text>Livia Drusa is a name referring to women of the Drusi branch of the Livia gens of ancient Rome, the name &quot;Drusa&quot; is a feminized form of the cognomen &quot;Drusus&quot;. It may refer to:

*Livia, wife of Publius Rutilius Rufus
*Livia, mother of Servilia and Cato the Younger
*Livia (died 29 AD), wife of Augustus, better known by the diminutive &quot;Livia Drusilla&quot;

